modules.description: Provides functions for compressing and decompressing data using the ZIP format, including reading and writing ZIP archives with support for file entries and compression methods. Works with byte sequences, file paths, and ZIP archive structures. Used to embed compressed resources in applications or efficiently store multiple files in a single archive.

Provides functions for compressing and uncompressing byte sequences using the zlib library, with support for custom input and output handlers. Works with byte arrays, strings, and a stream type that manages compression state. Used for efficiently compressing large data streams or decompressing compressed data in memory.

Reads and writes ZIP archives, handling entries with file names, compression levels, modification times, and comments. Processes entries as strings or channels, supporting direct data extraction and file writing. Enables adding new entries from strings, files, or channels, with control over compression and metadata.

Provides functions to decompress and compress data through input and output channels. Reads and writes characters, bytes, and buffers from gzip-compressed files or existing I/O channels. Used for handling compressed log files, streaming data over networks, and efficiently storing large datasets in compressed form.
